This paper is about evaluating and comparing AI agents in the context of General Video Game Playing. The paper proposes a set of metrics and a comparison method that can be applied to any agent regardless of its algorithmic nature. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of evolutionary computation techniques, tree search algorithms, hyper heuristic based or knowledge based algorithms, which are all common techniques in the field of Game Theory (cs.GT). The paper also mentions the decision making process of the AI agents, which is a topic of interest in the field of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Swarm Intelligence (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the shape of the agent decision landscape, which is related to the field of Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
